cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Scientific Claim Verification Engine"
version: 0.2.0
date-released: 2026-04-16
authors:
  - family-names: Perrelle
    given-names: Vivien
    affiliation: Locus Lab
repository-code: https://github.com/VivienP/scientific-claim-verification-engine
license: Apache-2.0
abstract: >
  An auditable pipeline for claim-by-claim verification of scientific text
  against cited source abstracts. Extracts verifiable claims via LLM,
  resolves citations via Semantic Scholar, and verifies each claim against
  its source abstract with structured LLM reasoning and full provenance logging.
keywords:
  - scientific verification
  - claim extraction
  - citation resolution
  - provenance
  - LLM
